<div class="jobs-header">
<div class="h1-extend"></div>
<div class="container">
<h1>Jobs @ Dev Bootcamp</h1>
</div>
</div>
 
 
<div class="jobs-summary">
<div class="container">
<h2>We're hiring in San Francisco, Chicago, and New York City</h2>
<p>
Our mission is to build the best learning environment for nurturing the next generation of web developers. We are looking for other tech- and education-minded folks to embark on this grand experiment with us.
</p>
<p>
<strong>Want to come play?</strong>
</p>
</div>
</div>
 
 
<div class="jobs">
<div class="container">
<div class="col-left">
<h2 id="open-positions">Open Positions</h2>
<div>
<div class="job-description">
<h3>Teacher</h3>
<p>
At DBC, we strive to always practice what we preach. Teachers lead by example, demonstrating their passion for learning and their commitment to a high standard of excellence.
</p>
<p>
Being a teacher at DBC is more like being a trekking guide or triathalon coach than a follow-the-textbook style lecturer. Teachers lead discussions, guide inquiry, pair program with students, emphasize the meta-skills and core concepts of software engineering, support students in their projects and challenges, and provide feedback to students and each other.
</p>
<p>
We think teaching is challenging, meaningful, and exceptionally fun. If you're up to the task, come join us.
</p>
<p><strong>Locations: San Francisco, Chicago, New York City</strong></p>
<p>
<strong>Send an email introducing yourself to
<a href="mailto:jobs@devbootcamp.com" class="call-to-action">jobs@devbootcamp.com</a>.</strong>
</p>
</div>
<div class="job-description">
<h3>NYC - Employer Partnerships</h3>
<p>
This role will lead DBC::NYC’s efforts to find rewarding and exciting career opportunities for graduates of DBC. The successful candidate will relish the challenges of building a large, expanding and loyal network of Bootcamp employer partners in NYC and the northeast corridor who count on Dev Bootcamp as their go-to destination to satisfy all their junior developer hiring needs. You will be a founding member (employee #5) of Dev Bootcamp’s growing Placement team.
</p>
<p>
Core Accountabilities<br>
<ul>
<li>Establish DBC as a beloved actor within the NYC tech sector by: (A) building DBC’s employer network (prospecting and business development), and (B) acting as the primary spokesperson for our recruiting model to employers and beyond.</li>
<li>Drive DBC revenue and maximize employer satisfaction by managing the placement of DBC’s graduates (matching students with employers)</li>
</ul>
</p>
<p>
Signs you are a great fit:<br>
<ul>
<li>You have 5 years experience in tech recruiting: preferably a reputable search firm.</li>
<li>You have an a large rolodex of high-trust relationships at existing NYC tech companies.</li>
<li>You think getting people into life-elevating career paths is your calling and our social mission of exquisite livelihood resonates deeply.</li>
<li>You are excited about the responsibilities, uncertainties and challenges that come with scaling a new type of recruiting model.</li>
<li>You are based in NYC or willing to relocate.</li>
</ul>
</p>
<p><strong>Location: New York City</strong></p>
<p>
<strong>Send an email introducing yourself to
<a href="mailto:jobs@devbootcamp.com" class="call-to-action">jobs@devbootcamp.com</a>.</strong>
</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="col-right">
<p><em>Dev Bootcamp is a choose-your-own-experience, bring-your-whole-self workplace. You choose when and how to work based on your passion, expertise, and values.</em></p>
<h3>Signs that you're the right fit for DBC</h3>
<ul>
<li>You have an equal love for machines, humans and the space between them.</li>
<li>Latent human potential makes you mad.</li>
<li>You believe that educating the whole person is a necessity, not a luxury.</li>
<li>You like fast-moving environments where experimentation is encouraged.</li>
<li>You're detail oriented, and OK with imperfection.</li>
<li>You take your work seriously, and yourself not so seriously.</li>
<li>You're a full stack web developer (familiar with ruby/rails), and consider yourself a life-long learner.</li>
<li>You're based in the SF Bay Area, Chicago, or New York City, or willing to relocate (we'll happily buy your bus ticket).</li>
</ul>
<h3>The Perks</h3>
<ul>
<li>Choose-your-own-experience! Want to work 39 weeks a year? Alternate between teaching and building? What about working part-time? Dev Bootcamp is designed to put you in control of your time.</li>
<li>Flexible time off. Vacation is provided in a take-what-you-need form. For teachers, we recommend 3 weeks off every 9 weeks. (Hey! Teaching is hard work!)</li>
<li>Health insurance, yoga, counseling and a free lunch every now and then.</li>
<li>Work alongside a growing group of warm-hearted, dedicated people who sincerely want to make a dent in the status quo.</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
</div>
 
 
